HEADWORD: En rapport
<hw>En` rap`port"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>In accord,
harmony, or sympathy; having a mutual, esp. a private, understanding; of
a hypnotic subject, being in such a mental state as to be especially
subject to the influence of a particular person or persons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enrapt</ent>⟦br⟧
